6. Technological Civilization Beyond Earth
One of the key technological developments that may enable an existence-oriented civilization is the emergence of autonomous technological infrastructure.
Historically, industrial systems have depended heavily on human labor and planetary ecosystems.
However, advances in robotics, artificial intelligence, and automated manufacturing may eventually enable self-sustaining industrial systems.
